post_text:
AUSTINTOWN ROTARY PROVIDES SEVEN SCHOLARSHIPS TO FITCH STUDENTS

Seven Fitch seniors were awarded funds of nearly $3000 by the Rotary Club of Austintown. Known as the William Courtney Scholarships in honor of a long term member who donated to such projects, this annual donation helps worthy students who are active in the community based on an essay written by each on the impact of their school involvement upon their future plans. Three of the seven attended the recent Rotary meeting to speak of their college decisions and majors.

Pictured above left to right front are Alexi Blessing, Cecilia Segretario, and Julia Brooks. In the back are incoming Rotary President Heather Fronk and outgoing past President Chris Vlosich. Other winners not pictured are Kelsey King, Ellie Layton, Jessica Silvestri and Ashleigh Warmouth.

2020 has been hard on us all. For those graduating this year, many of the things that we got to experience our senior year have not been an option. Sports took a major hit. The Austintown Fitch Baseball and Softball teams started practicing but never got to have a season. As a way to send their seniors off in style, a slow pitch softball game was organized pitting the players against their coaches and parents. I was honored to get to attend and capture some of the highlights. Feel free to share this video with the families of those who played.

Make sure you like our page for more community videos!

Those order ordered Autism Awareness T-shirts from Fitch HS can pick up their shirt order from FHS on Wednesday morning from 10-12 at Door M which is in the staff parking lot on the southwest corner near the art wing. Drivers will not have to get out of their cars. Orders can be placed in the trunk.

Alternatively, orders can be picked up Thursday from 6-7 pm in the AIS parking lot near the student pickup area. Again, drivers will not need to get out of their cars.

Questions or concerns should be directed to Mrs. Caruso at rcaruso@austintownschools.org

Thank you to everyone who supported our project of autism awareness.
